DPRK commodity exhibition opens in Cambodia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- A DPRK commodity exhibition was opened at the Cambodian National Cultural Center on March 25 with due ceremony.
 Present at the ceremony were officials of the ministry of culture and arts of Cambodia, The DPRK ambassador to Cambodia, its embassy officials and cultural officials of various countries.
 Noting that the Korean people have achieved great progress not only in the cultural field but all other spheres under the wise guidance of leader Kim Jong Il, minister of culture and arts Norodom Bopha Devi said that Cambodian king Norodom Sihanouk was paying great attention to the development of the friendly relations with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She expressed belief that the ties of cooperation in the cultural and art field between the two peoples would grow stronger and develop in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the participants went round the exhibition.

Defending national sovereignty called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The Bush administration torpedoed multi-faceted negotiations and contacts, scuppered the DPRK-U.S. agreed framework and has pursued confrontation and war against the DPRK, while obstructing the inter-Korean dialogue and the implementation of the north-south joint declaration.
 In this regard Minju Joson today in a signed commentary says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation on the Korean Peninsula has reached an extreme pitch of tension and the danger of a new war is increasing owing to an adventurous anti-DPRK line of the bellicose bush group and its war moves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent policy of the DPRK to prevent a war and defend peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We want peace, not a war. There is no reason for the compatriots in the north and the south to fight each other. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But it is our revolutionary stand not to allow anyone to infringe upon our sovereignty and dignity, wantonly challenging our peace-loving efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists' moves for aggression and war and their presence in South Korea are the basic factor of disturbing peace and barring the peaceful reunification of Korea and the root cause of bringing a nuclear holocaust to the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. imperialists are allowed to carry on their war moves and perpetuate their forces' presence in South Korea, a new war will engulf our country and put the nation's destiny and the future of our country in danger. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Had the DPRK failed to increase the national defence capability and follow an army-based policy, The U.S. imperialists would have ignited a new war in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army-based policy is a true patriotic policy to defend the nation's security and the country's peace. This has been clearly proved by the present reality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army-based policy is aimed to defend and glorify the socialist system and mount a fierce attack upon and deal merciless blows at the aggressors.

Declaration on present situation issued 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- 790 teachers of primary, middle and high schools in South Jolla Province, South Korea, under the "national teachers union" reportedly issued a declaration on the present situation on march 26 in support of the struggle of the unionists.
 Expressing absolute support to the members of the power industry trade union in their strike and the formation of the civil servants union, the declaration urged the authorities to immediately halt their crackdown on the strike and honestly approach the dialogue with the trade union. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It denounced the authorities for their policy of privatizing public enterprises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also accused them of refusing to recognize the civil servants union, dismissing its formation as "illegal." The declaration said that they would encourage the struggle of the workers of the power industry and the civil servants union and actively support them.

Implementation of June 15 joint declaration urged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The reunification solidarity for the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration and peace on the Korean Peninsula (Thongil Ryondae) reportedly sponsored a press conference against war and for the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration beside the U.S. embassy in Seoul on March 27.
 The press conference was held after rev. Han Sang Ryol, permanent representative of Thongil Ryondae, staged a hunger sit-in in front of the U.S. embassy for 8 days from March 20. It was called to denounce the U.S. moves to turn the Korean Peninsula into a theatre of war and harden the will to implement the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rev. Han released an article titled "finishing up the hunger sit-in opposing South Korea-U.S. joint military exercises, war exercise and urging the repentance and withdrawal of the U.S." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
During the period of his hunger strike he reaffirmed that the way out of the Korean nation is, first of all, to implement the June 15 joint declaration, he said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint declaration is a watershed of a new history liquidating the times of division and opening an era of reunification and a great programme and milestone of the reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A paper of the press conference was read out.

Cancellation of plan to introduce fighters demanded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- Different South Korean organizations reportedly released statements assailing the virtually confirmed plan to introduce U.S.-made fighters.
 The "national alliance for democracy and reunification" accused the present authorities and the "Ministry of National Defense" of South Korea of working hard to purchase "F-15K" fighters without fail, yielding to the pressure put by the U.S. upon them to buy its weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization said that the authorities keen to purchase U.S.-made weapons under "South Korea-U.S. cooperation system" are playing into the hands of Washington seeking to cool down the inter-Korean ties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The social democratic union noted that the authorities' unpopular U.S.-toeing flunkeyist selection of the outdated type of fighters under its coercion must be dismissed as treachery worse than that of traitor Ri Wan Yong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is our belief that it is the only way of preventing the repetition of such shameful treachery to force the U.S. troops to pull out of South Korea and thus win back national sovereignty and achieve the independent reunification, the statement added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It urged the present "government" to immediately withdraw the decision made on the selection of the type of fighters and abrogate the "South Korea-U.S. mutual defense pact."

Russian presidential orchestra enjoys performance of KPA merited choir 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The Russian presidential orchestra yesterday appreciated a performance of the merited choir of the Korean People's Army (KPA) at the Mansudae Art Theatre.
 Present on invitation were the members of the orchestra headed by lieutenant general Sergei Streigin, commander of the garrison of the Kremlin in Moscow, Andrei Karlov, Russian ambassador to the DPRK, and embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was seen by Kim Kuk Thae, Kim Ki Nam, Kim Yong Sun, secretaries of the c.c., the Workers' Party of Korea, KPA general Pak Jae Gyong, leading officials of party and power organs, and the press, artistes and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The choir sang Russian songs such as "Vast Land of Siberia" and "Just War," leaving deep impressions on the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russian songs "Forward" and "Our friendship will be everlasting" were sung by the choir conducted by Russian people's artiste P.B. Obshannikov who is the chief conductor of the orchestra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was acclaimed by the audience for its high ideological and artistic value.
